values: Long morning walk, lots of coffee, mostly watched youtube
got sloppy on a couple things at work. both surfaced today but one was made yesterday. some trouble sleeping, worried about mom's procedure. Impulsively bought chiliblanket and a new watch

took mom to and from the hospital, no bad news. Very light work at beginning of the day, ramped up at end of day, ended up staying on till after 7. Ayesha mentioned she was happy with my performance on a call
replanted herbs into bigger pot, very relieved to find out moms symptoms have been abating. replaced car air filter. quick workout. bath

tried out unforced meditation, felt good like my mind got sorted out and was less scattered. weird day at work. Ayesha closed a some pull requests even after I told her why they were necessary. I decided to just let it be. ive been feeling like I'm in a bit of a funk and didnt feel like making the case, didnt feel the confidence that i could make a coherent case. Some leg strength movements before chinese dinner, last episode of GoT, cake and cereal and fruit as a late night snack. woke up feeling like shit

disrupted sleep due to back pain but actually woke up feeling pretty good, maybe due to the huperzine. long unforced meditation went well, felt more relaxing and I was able to settle in and concentrate more on the present moment without too many thoughts interrupting, likely due to the reduced moda. learned some python- decided to read my way through a tutorial rather than watch one, found it more stimulating and informative and less passive. followed a lower back yoga youtube that helped loosen me up a lot. had an actual conversation with my mom over dinner
Ayesha and Miranda let me update the compare page's vue app with no convincing. Took a walk after work with mom and mark, had a pleasant time talking. Spent the evening in my room

slept poorly. woke up around 3 because i had to take a shit. solid work day regardless, had a clever solution to a pr update that wasnt exactly what Miranda wanted but accomplished what she meant. received chiliblanket
woke up at 430 again, really felt run down, better after a nap. boring work day with more pointless meetings. really feeling disconnected and anhedonic. hoping my weekend trip shakes things up

Had an odd second wind around 9pm, did some research on python/whoop integrations, got distracted and shopped around a bit for a new note app. Liked the idea of roam, but the web only format was offputting and settled on Notion

Small amount of work, got some actual python code in place for whooper. Pretty sore from yesterdays workout. Big stock market drop today made me more sure that the way to go is to earn through software, also consider more seriously taking some more option positions. Probably drank too much coffee- I've been feeling jittery, unfocused and easily irritable. really hot bath

Woke up around 4 again last night, could be due to overheating. My room was a little warmer than the rest of the house and my chilipad was 4 deg higher than what it was set to. Opened the window and fell back asleep. Felt groggy in the morning

Mom went out of town for the day and overnight. Had a nice little cheat day bender. Bummed about getting the error handling removed that I worked so hard on for the dynamic pricing. The beurocracy's starting to bum me out. Still a great job. Did some thinking and concluded that I'm probably overreacting and being ungrateful

Tried the weighted blanket again, woke up roasting. Posted a negative review in the hopes a customer service rep will offer some kind of restitution. Probably end up just returning it. Feel like shit and a little embarrased at how much ive been drinking. Decided to go the whole month of November without drinking.
Woke up feeling really refreshed, significantly diminished need for caffeine/moda. Long really pleasant run. Some light work but spent most productive time on whooper python

Decided to focus on concurrently learning the basics of python and the ststistics involved in DS. I guess im valuing the ability to get a more interesting and lucrative job over the less probable scenario where I'd make a bunch of money writing shopify apps

Changed my mind about the data science/stats focus. Sstill gonna round out my full stack skills learning python. DS would be nice but it just seems a little seperate from my core set of known skills, which not only makes it more uncertain that I'd enjoy the work, but makes breaking into the field a much tougher task

A lot of good work done on Whooper. Visited Dad just to say hi, he was having a bad day according to mom so I didn't stay long. Just realized I'm having way fewer of those dead days where I don't feel like doing anything after stopping drinking
Just a really relaxing day. Only did what I felt like doing and had a really nice time
Had an oddly impulsive day. Bought a bunch of stuff and committed to CM's D&I Northstar initiative without asking what exactly it was

slept poorly due to some back pain. work was kind of a mess due to everyone rushing to get the PL updates out tomorrow. I think I did well though. got a bunch of tasks pertaining to tightening up error handling for dynamic pricing and didnt get any pr feedback, but did notice that Miranda updated the mac compare app with some extra checks to make sure the user entered valid id's. felt strangely perturbed by that
